				<td colspan="2"><span>Has worked great for me pre-50 using TDoK (lvl 41 now).  It certainly doesn't work on all mobs.. but the author never said it did.  It's a great tip!  Just remember however, one lag spike, one stun, and you're dead if you have 12+ mobs on you.. but that happens even if you're not autocircling.  I don't bite off more than I can chew however.. I'm trying to grab at least 7 mobs atm.. going up as I level vs. the type of mobs I'm killing (Spirocs).  That way I can take a couple hits if there is a lag spike.  Once you hit lvl 50, by my calculations, you need to be AEing at least 7 mobs at once for the damage to be worth it (unless you're not using drums at all and are using an extremely powerful horn), sounds pretty hard to me.. at least until you get DA.  I'm going to try swarm kiting at 50.
<br />

<br />
P.S. no noob is going to be kiting in HoH.. this guide has certainly helped my newbie bard.  Read Taiisien's guides for mobs to kill that work with this technique.  Also, I highly suggest turning down your settings to avoid lag, but leave clip plane alone or you might miss an add or something.</span></td>
